      prompt: `<div>A right rectangular prism has a height of 24 inches. The length of the prism’s base is x inches, which is 10 inches more than the width of the prism’s base. Which function V gives the volume of the prism, in cubic inches, in terms of the length of the prism’s base?</div>`,
